&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Vestwell is the financial technology company powering the new savings economy. Our platform redefines how people save for the critical aspects of life across retirement, education, and healthcare savings needs. Today, Vestwell enables over 350,000 businesses and over 2M active savers, with over $50B in assets saved across all 50 states.&amp;nbsp;Vestwell&#39;s platform serves a diverse clientele, including financial advisers, employers, third-party administrators, financial institutions, payroll providers, government agencies, and individual savers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To learn more, visit &lt;a href=&quot;http://vestwell.com/&quot;&gt;vestwell.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;TITLE: 529 Business Intelligence Specialist&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;DUTIES: Apply knowledge of 529 and CSA plan mechanics, regulatory rules, and financial processing&lt;br&gt;to ensure compliant and accurate reporting. Identify and resolve data discrepancies and&lt;br&gt;unexpected system behavior. Manage end‑to‑end reporting cycles.Design data models,&lt;br&gt;queries, and governed analytics. Collaborate with engineering and product teams to enhance&lt;br&gt;data pipelines and support client-established standards. Communicate regulatory and&lt;br&gt;technical requirements to clients. Develop automation to replace manual reporting&lt;br&gt;processes and reduce turnaround time. Manage reporting requests, draft Jira epics and&lt;br&gt;stories, define requirements, and establish acceptance criteria. Document workflows, data&lt;br&gt;models, and quality control procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SALARY: $105,00.00-$110,000.00 per year&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;SCHEDULE: 40 hours per week, Monday through Friday (9:00am-5:00pm)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;LOCATION: 640 Freedom Business Center Drive, 2nd Floor, King of Prussia, PA, 19406&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;REQUIREMENTS: Bachelor’s degree, or the foreign equivalent, in Computer Science,&lt;br&gt;Information Systems, Product Design, or closely related. plus 3 years of&lt;br&gt;experience in product development in client-driven scenarios. Providing&lt;br&gt;and managing recon tooling for tracking activity anomalies at any point in&lt;br&gt;the processing life-cycle. Minimum 2 years of experience with 529 &amp;amp;amp; CSA&lt;br&gt;plan mechanics, including financial processing rules, market cycles, and&lt;br&gt;program limitations. 3 years of experience with the following (which may&lt;br&gt;have been gained concurrently): SQL, Sigma/Tableau, Jira, Agile&lt;br&gt;methodology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CONTACT: Patty Kim, Vestwell Holdings, Inc., 360 Madison Ave, 15 th Floor, New York, NY&lt;br&gt;10017&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OUR BENEFITS&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We’re an innovative, high-growth company with an exciting future ahead. At Vestwell, we prioritize employee wellbeing through comprehensive health benefits, generous time off, and a dedicated Employee Wellbeing Committee. Our hybrid work model offers flexibility while providing access to our collaborative offices in Midtown Manhattan, Austin, King of Prussia, and Scottsdale. And, of course, as a company focused on helping people save for the future, we offer a competitive 401(k) plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OUR PROCESS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our interview process starts the same for every candidate with 1-2 introductory conversations to learn more about your background, interests, and what you&#39;re looking for, while also giving you the opportunity to learn more about Vestwell and the team. From there, the process varies by role but typically includes a skills or experience-based assessment, such as a coding interview, portfolio review, or deeper discussion of your relevant experience. Successful candidates then move on to a virtual or in-person interview panel. Before extending an offer, we

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Vestwell is the financial technology company powering the new savings economy. Our platform redefines how people save for the critical aspects of life across retirement, education, and healthcare savings needs. Today, Vestwell enables over 350,000 businesses and over 2M active savers, with over $50B in assets saved across all 50 states.&amp;nbsp;Vestwell&#39;s platform serves a diverse clientele, including financial advisers, employers, third-party administrators, financial institutions, payroll providers, government agencies, and individual savers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To learn more, visit &lt;a href=&quot;http://vestwell.com/&quot;&gt;vestwell.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who Are We Looking For?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and highly organized professional to join our Investment Operations team as an Operations Associate. This person will be responsible for coordinating the setup of investment products and programs with our partner custodians, advisors, fund/insurance companies, and investment managers. They will be responsible for managing internal and external communications around investments with various stakeholders including clients, vendors, and partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While primarily operational in nature, our team sits at a unique intersection of clients, operations, and strategy, and the role reflects this multifaceted nature. The job requires keen attention to detail and ability to track multiple projects and communicate with 3rd parties across multiple platforms.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Will You Be Doing?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this position you’ll be responsible for a number of items, as it pertains to the investment management operational oversight and implementation. The job responsibilities will include but are not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnering with our plan sales and implementations teams to vet and implement the investment options for plans being brought onto the Vestwell platform; this includes both cost and asset class coverage analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating with our custody partners to ensure a seamless new plan onboarding process&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaising with Fund and Insurance companies to ensure appropriate processes are in place for making funds available within plans&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with 3rd party investment managers and advisors to define onboarding and ongoing requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring investment options are in sync with the respective programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring investment performance and fact sheets are updated regularly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in key quality assurance processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Necessities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ year of experience in a Financial Services, or related industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to understand the “big picture” and the importance of the team’s role in the overall process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills across internal stakeholders and external partner groups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for learning and applying new concepts, and bridging information where continued process-development is key&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to self-manage around tight deadlines in a fast-paced environment while ensuring the integrity and accuracy of the details&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical proficiency using Excel and process management tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Extras&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intermediate SQL skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience within financial services, with a focus on investment operations and fund implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
